        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali139-kilavi">itu maṭalēṟukiṉṟa talaivaṉ cāṉṟōrkkuk kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali139">
              <l>cāṉṟavir vāḻiyō cāṉṟavi reṉṟum</l>
              <l>piṟarnōyun tannōypōṟ pōṟṟi yaṟaṉaṟital </l>
              <l>cāṉṟavark kellāṅ kaṭaṉāṉā livvirunta</l>
              <l>cāṉṟī rumakkoṉ ṟaṟivuṟuppeṉ māṉṟa</l>
              <l>tuḷiyiṭai miṉṉuppōṟ ṟōṉṟi yorutti</l>
              <l>yoḷiyō ṭuruveṉṉaik kāṭṭi yaḷiyaḷeṉ</l>
              <l>ṉeñcāṟu koṇṭā ḷataṟkoṇṭun tuñcē</l>
              <l>ṉaṇiyalaṅ kāviraip pūvō ṭerukkiṉ</l>
              <l>piṇaiyalaṅ kaṇṇi milaintu maṇiyārppa</l>
              <l>vōṅkirum peṇṇai maṭalūrnteṉ ṉevvanōy</l>
              <l>tāṅkuta ṟēṟṟā viṭumpaik kuyirppāka</l>
              <l>vīṅkiḻai mātar tiṟattoṉṟu nīṅkātu</l>
              <l>pāṭuveṉ pāymā niṟuttu;</l>
              <l rend="space">yāmattu mellaiyu mevvat tiraiyalaippa</l>
              <l>māmēlē ṉeṉṟu maṭalpuṇaiyā nīntuvēṉ</l>
              <l>ṟēmoḻi māta ruṟāa tuṟīiya</l>
              <l>kāmak kaṭalakap paṭṭu;</l>
              <l rend="space">uyyā varunōyk kuyavāku maiya</l>
              <l>luṟīiyā ḷīttavim mā;</l>
              <l rend="space">kāṇuna reḷḷak kalaṅkit talaivante</l>
              <l>ṉāṇeḻiṉ muṟṟi yuṭaittuḷ ḷaḻittaru</l>
              <l>māṇiḻai mātarā ḷēereṉak kāmaṉa</l>
              <l>tāṇaiyāl vanta paṭai; </l>
              <l rend="space">kāmak kaṭumpakaiyiṟ ṟōṉṟiṉēṟ kēma</l>
              <l>meḻiṉuta līttavim mā;</l>
              <l rend="space">akaiyeri yāṉāteṉ ṉāruyi reñcum</l>
              <l>vakaiyiṉā luḷḷañ cuṭutaru maṉṉō</l>
              <l>mukaiyē rilaṅkeyiṟ ṟiṉṉakai mātar</l>
              <l>takaiyāṟ ṟalaikkoṇṭa neñcu;</l>
              <l rend="space">aḻaṉmaṉṟa kāma varunōy niḻaṉmaṉṟa</l>
              <l>nēriḻai yīttavim mā;</l>
              <l rend="space">āṅkatai,</l>
              <l>aṟintaṉi rāyiṟ cāṉṟavir tāṉṟava</l>
              <l>morīit tuṟakkattiṉ vaḻīi yāṉṟō</l>
              <l>ruḷḷiṭap paṭṭa varacaṉaip peyarttava</l>
              <l>ruyarnilai yulaka muṟīi yāṅkeṉ</l>
              <l>ṟuyarnilai tīrtta ṉuntalaik kaṭaṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
              <l corresp="1">Worthy people, oh worthy people. Always</l>
              <l corresp="2a-c">honouring the pain of others like their own pain</l>
              <l corresp="2d-3c">because it is the duty of all worthy people to know [their] duty,</l>
              <l corresp="3d-4c">I will have you worthy people who are here know one thing:</l>
              <l corresp="4d-5">appearing like a flash in midst the confuse drops, one lady</l>
              <l corresp="6">showed [her] form to me with brightness, pitiful one</l>
              <l corresp="7">[and] took the way to my heart. Taking that in I don’t sleep.</l>
              <l>Wearing a pretty chaplet [and] a binding of Yarcum</l>
              <l corresp="8f">along with ornate swaying Āvirai flowers, as bell ring</l>
              <l corresp="10a-c">having mounted the stems of the high dark palmyra tree, </l>
              <l corresp="10d-11">while there is a sigh for the distress that does not make clear my bearing troublesome pain, </l>
              <l corresp="12">without leaving out one thing with respect to the woman with taught jewels,</l>
              <l corresp="13">I sing, having set up [my] leaping horse:</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>While waves of trouble slap [me] midnight and day,</l>
              <l>saying “I am on a horse” I swim with a palmyra stem as a raft,</l>
              <l>being caught in the sea of passion</l>
              <l corresp="14-17">that is caused by the woman with sweet words not having [me].</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>This horse which was given by her who caused</l>
              <l corresp="18-19">[my] infatuation that is an escape from [this] pain difficult to escape from.</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>While onlookers ridicule [me], stirring up, meeting [me]</l>
              <l>it has completely broken my male handsomeness,</l>
              <l>the weapon that came by the order of Kāma </l>
              <l corresp="20-23">as the beauty of that woman with glorious jewels who destroyed [me] inside.</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>It is protection for me who whom it appeared as a fierce weapon against passion,</l>
              <l corresp="24-25">this horse that was given by [her with] graceful forehead.  </l>
              <l></l>
              <l>As burning flames do not end, my difficult/precious life [just] remains.</l>
              <l>In [that way] will it burn inside,</l>
              <l>my heart that suitable met</l>
              <l corresp="26-29">the woman with sweet smile [and] bud-like shining teeth?  </l>
              <l></l>
              <l>Fire indeed the difficult pain of passion. Shade indeed </l>
              <l corresp="30-31">is this horse she with fine jewels gave [me].</l>
              <l></l>
              <l corresp="32">Thus,</l>
              <l></l>
              <l>you who know that, worthy people,</l>
              <l>like of those who make the king who fell again </l>
              <l>have the world of high status, to be placed among</l>
              <l>noble men after he renounced penance [and] missed heaven,</l>
              <l corresp="33-37">to end my state of misery is the duty on your heads.</l>
            </lg>
